Job Description
ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Preparing, instructing and grading all class coursework;
Assigning final grades;
Maintaining regularly scheduled office hours to meet with students.
QUALIFICATIONS, KNOWLEDGE, AND SKILL REQUIREMENTS:
Master’s degree with a minimum of 18 graduate level credits in the discipline of Fire Science from an accredited institution;
Certification as a Florida Firefighter or eligibility for certification;
Florida Fire Standard Certification to instruct certifiable classes or eligibility to receive certification;
Five (5) years of proven work experience as a firefighter;
A proven track record of effective instruction in Fire Science with the ability to utilize contemporary technology;
The ability to function in an occupationally-oriented program requiring regular interfacing with students, secondary schools, and fire service agencies;
Documentation of successful on-the-job experiences in the contemporary workplace;
A willingness to apply technology and innovative approaches to the teaching of Fire Science is essential;
All instructors must meet the appropriate credentialing requirements for the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools (SACS).
SPECIFIC DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Instructing fire science courses leading to the Associate in Science Degree;
Instructing in the Basic Recruit Firefighting Academy;
Serving as a liaison and resource to the fire service community and public school systems of the service district;
Serving on college committees as assigned, marketing the program; serving as an advisor to a vocational advisory committee; academic advisement to students;
Reviewing and revising curriculum to meet mandated changes or industry needs;
Appropriately integrating computer software and technology-based instruction;
Maintaining a safe and effective classroom environment;
Participating in department, division, and adjunct faculty meetings;
Performing other duties and responsibilities as assigned.
PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:
This position requires an ability to sit, stand, walk, bend, reach up, stoop, ability to participate in physical activities related to firefighting, the ability to lift an object of fifty (50) pounds or less, and carry items occasionally in excess of fifty (50) pounds. It also requires manual dexterity to operate standard office machines, such as, copier, fax, calculator, telephone, and other equipment as necessary. IRSC expects its employees to follow proper safety standards while employed by the College.
